<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="229" type="distribution">
<caption inLine="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="229" startId="2.[1004,1235,1255,1294]" targetBox="[179,976,775,1336]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[1004,1803,778,1347]" lastBlockId="2.[178,1801,1359,2243]" pageId="2" pageNumber="229">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1004,1242,1255,1294]" pageId="2" pageNumber="229">Distribution.</emphasis>
Endemic to S Arabian Peninsula, recorded from a narrow coastal strip in SE 
<collectingCountry box="[289,419,1359,1398]" name="Yemen" pageId="2" pageNumber="229">Yemen</collectingCountry>
and SW 
<collectingCountry box="[589,711,1359,1398]" name="Oman" pageId="2" pageNumber="229">Oman</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="229" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[178,1801,1359,2243]" pageId="2" pageNumber="229">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[181,523,1412,1451]" pageId="2" pageNumber="229">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 41-60 mm, tail 16-29 mm, ear 14-22 mm, hindfoot 8-10 mm, forearm 43-1-46-5 mm; weight 6-13 g. Muzzle of the Arabian Trident Leafnosed Bat is relatively short with large, distinctive noseleaf that has three subtriangular projections from its posterior margin. Pelage is beige or pale brownish gray dorsally, somewhat paler ventrally. Dental formula for all members of all species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1615,1731,1625,1664]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Asellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="229" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Asellia</taxonomicName>
is I 1/2, C 1/1, P 1/2, M 3/3 (x2) = 28.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[180,1620,1731,1770]" pageId="2" pageNumber="229" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[178,1801,1359,2243]" box="[180,1620,1731,1770]" pageId="2" pageNumber="229">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[180,331,1731,1770]" pageId="2" pageNumber="229">Habitat.</emphasis>
Coastal arid savanna and shrubland of southern Arabian Peninsula.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
